title: Garmin - City Navigator North America NT 2018.30 Unlocked IMG
description: Garmin Navigator 2018.30 maps, released 10/11/2017 Current as of 11/04/2017 CN North America NT 2018.30 Full Coverage of North America Works on my 255w, and should work on all older units that don't check for cracked maps Some devices only work with older non SDHC SD cards, 4GB-8GB in size. If it doesn't work, try a smaller SD card. If your Garmin has enough internal space: Rename gmapsupp.img to gmapprom.img and replace it with the one that is on the internal memory. If your Garmin doesn't have enough internal space, or you don't want to delete the original maps: 1) Format an SD card as FAT32 2) Make a folder on the SD card called "Garmin" (without the quotation marks) 3) Copy gmapsupp.img to the Garmin folder on the SD card Once the unlocked maps are on your device, and the SD card is inserted, turn the device on and make sure the new maps are selected under Tools>Settings>Map>Map Info You can also get it to work on newer devices by patching their firmware following this guide: http://www.navitotal.com/topic17987.html Once your newer device has the firmware patched, you can use my maps on all Garmin devices
